  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight by analyzing the statistical patterns of discovered failures and linking them to model internals. The authors assess the diversity of erroneous behaviors by measuring how many output classes are affected by mispredictions and by calculating the scaled entropy across these classes. This constitutes an analysis of statistical failure patterns (e.g., class-level error concentration). The paper also links the effectiveness of its fuzzing guidance in finding faults to a model's internal property—\"neuron entanglement\"—which the proposed NLC metric is designed to capture. However, the analysis does not extend to explaining why these failures occur by linking them to specific, underlying model vulnerabilities like reliance on spurious features, dataset bias, or overfitting.",
